My sincere thanks for all the folks who wrote.  I got a number of 
great responses including a great link on how to get the lock apart. 
As I was laying out my tolls for that job, in comes this simple idea 
I should not have missed from Bob -- IT WORKED!!!!!
>
>well if the key went in it should come out,  sounds like a tumble is
>sticking.  I would squirt some WD40 or similar down in the key slot
>(disconnect the battery) if the key can be worked loose ok, if not I would
>then let some light oil drip into the cyl and continue to work the key up
>and down, you want to get the key out in the off position if you can...
>
>then when you get it out, get a key made to the key code on the lock and
>squirt some graphite in the keyhole and use the new key, your key is
>probably worn
>
>>  quick way to pop the lock without removing the steering wheel, etc.?
>>  Or a known way to release the tumblers?  Also, the key I have is the
>>  ONLY key to the back gate which is now locked.  Arrrrgh!
>
>oh yeah, unlock the rear hatch when you get the key out
>
>Bob

Thanks Bob, and everyone else for their kind responses and not 
calling me names for forgetting to lubricate the locks!  They are all 
well-oiled now!

